did.unittitle: David Rockefeller Personal and Professional papers, Memoirs, RG 7

physdesc.extent: 103 letter document boxes, 3 legal document boxes, 7 microfilm reels (16mm) and 1 record storage box.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This is a collection of materials used and created in the prepartion of David Rockefeller's Memoris, including books of clippings from newspapers and periodicals that document the interests and activities of David Rockefeller through the 1980s, including his retirement from Chase Manhattan Bank in 1980.

The collection also includes research materials such as chronologies of David Rockefeller's activities and pertinent events, project ideas and chapter drafts, summaries of philanthropic activites and donations, political contributions, correspondence and transcripts of interviews with David Rockefeller and significant contemporaries, as well as documentation of preprations for book tour appearances accompanying release of Memoirs.

There is also a small selection of biographical materials, including correspondence with Peggy Rockefeller, correspondence with his parents John D. Rockefeller Jr. and Abby Aldrich Rockefeller, documentation of educational activities including David Rockefeller's childhood experience at the Lincoln School, and his education at Harvard University and the London School of Economics.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Original order, as received. Materials are arranged in three series. Series 1: Clipping Books, Microfilm. Series 2: Clipping Books, Papers. Series 3: Research.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The microfilm was created by the staff of Room 5600, the Rockefeller family office at Rockefeller Center, and transferred to the Rockefeller Archive Center in the early 1980s.

physdesc.extent: 48 letter document boxes, 1 legal document box and 1 record storage box.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Cliiping Books primarily consist of newspaper articles, magazines and other periodicals. Many of the clipping books also contain materials consistent with traditional scrapbooks such as photographs, snapshots, programs, event announcements, awards, dinners, luncheons, and attendees lists. This series also contains a small set of Rockefeller family photograph albums and scrapbooks owned by David and Peggy Rockefeller.
